Algorithm findSum(A, z)
  Input: an ordered array A of n integers, an integer z
  Output: return true if there are i and j (i != j) such that A[i] + A[j] == z
          return false, otherwise
  Note that: This version is provided by Niranrith Saingern (CN #1) 4510520077.
             His algorithm performs in O(n) [better than my solution].

  left = 0
  right = n-1
  while (left < right)
  {
     while (A[left] + A[right] >= z)
     {
        if (A[left] + A[right] == z)
         return true
        right--
     }
     left++

     while ((A[left] + A[right] <= z) && (left < right))
     {
        if (A[left] + A[right] == z)
         return true
        left++
     }
     right--
  }
  return false
//O(n)
